.SH NAME
HTMLInputElement.step \- HTMLInputElement: step property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]step\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]HTMLInputElement\f[R] interface indicates the step by which
numeric or date\-time \f[CR]<input>\f[R] elements can change.
It reflects the element\[cq]s \f[CR]step\f[R] attribute.
Valid values include the string \f[CR]\[dq]any\[dq]\f[R] or a string
containing a positive floating point number.
If the attribute is not explicitly set, the \f[CR]step\f[R] property is
an empty string.
.SH VALUE
A string representing the element\[cq]s \f[CR]step\f[R] value or an
empty string if no step is explicitly set.
.SH EXAMPLE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] inputElement = document.querySelector(\[aq][type=\[dq]number\[dq]]\[aq]);
console.log(inputElement.step); \f[I]// the current value of the step attribute\f[R]
inputElement.step = 0.1; \f[I]// sets the step value to \[dq]0.1\[dq]\f[R]
inputElement.step = \[dq]any\[dq]; \f[I]// sets the step to \[dq]any\[dq]\f[R]
.EE
